11 Hubert Street, south east corner Collister Street between Hubert and Beach Street, east side; showing P.S. 44.

Board of Education, N.Y.C.
 1920.

Hubert Street, south side, west from Collister and across Greenwich Streets, showing the latter with the Ninth Ave. Elevated Line thereon. No. 11-13 Hubert Street, the 6-story warehouse at the S.W. corner of Collister Street (shown on left) will be demolished.

August 2, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

Hubert Street, north side, east from Collister to Hudson Streets, showing a 3-story former stable of the American Express Co. The 6-story structure on the right is No. 151 Hudson Street at the N.W. corner.

August 2, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.
